bpmn-setting.about-sign-privileges-detailed:
"One-vote system" details:
1. The follow-up processing mode is "direct processing"
  1.1. When setting a user, the approval is "agree", and the effect is "one-vote consent", that is, "countersign the task" after the user's approval It will directly end the downward flow and the "countersign node" status is "agree";
  1.2. When setting a user, the approval is "opposed", and the effect is "one-vote veto", that is, when the user approves, the "countersign task" will directly end the flow downward and the status of "countersign node" is "against";
In addition to the above settings, when a user sets up a batch of users, the countersign approval task can be ended and the flow down after the first approver approves it.
2. The follow-up processing mode is "waiting for everyone to vote"
  2.1. When a user is set up, other participants need to approve after the user approves it, but the end state of the "countersign node" has been approved by the user as the result;
  2.2. When setting up a batch of users, other participants also need to approve after the batch of users is approved, but the end state of the "countersign node" is the result of the approval button of the first user in the batch.

5. For the same field, configure the colors of "Background" and "Font" in multiple batches at the same time;

Only: Configure this field rule, other unconfigured fields will be displayed on the reverse output page, such as: there are three fields A\B\C, of which only "A" is set to display, other unconfigured fields B\C are all hidden, and the configuration is hidden "A", then B\C is displayed.

help.about-accordion-effect-detailed: Accordion effect, only one panel can be expanded at a time, and the other panels will shrink.
help.about-accuracy-detailed: For the decimal places of the number type, the precision value must be a non-negative integer and cannot be less than the decimal place of the step.
help.about-adaptive-content-detailed: By setting the [Adaptive Content] property, the height of the text field can be automatically adjusted according to the text content, and [Adaptive Content] can also be set as an object to specify the minimum number of lines and the maximum number of lines.
help.about-altitude-interval-detailed: 1) The current configuration item is adapted to the upper and lower intervals between the controls in the current grid layout.</br> 2) Add the configured bottom margin for all the controls in the grid layout, in pixels (px).
help.about-arrangement-detailed: You can set the options for this field, whether to sort horizontally or vertically.</br> Horizontal sorting can save form space and make the layout more compact;</br> Vertical sorting is more suitable for scenarios with a large number of options.
help.about-association-properties-detailed: Configure the associated attribute control to reference a field of other forms, and follow the field value corresponding to the associated form to change in real time. The field type of the setting field must be [Text].
help.about-back-end-verification: About the form submission backend verification check
help.about-back-end-verification-detailed: The submission setting is the limit of the form submission action.</br> Enable back-end verification: The verification of the back-end of the form will be verified to avoid bypassing the front-end verification and invalid data.</br> Turn on submission conflict reminder: Turn on conflict reminder to avoid repeated submission of forms, and the backend uses optimistic locking for processing.
help.about-background-picture-detailed: You can upload a picture as the background picture of the form. The recommended image size is: 1900x960
help.about-batch-detailed: The smaller the batch number, the higher the priority of the form rules. When the rules of a certain batch are met, all the rules of the current batch can be filtered. When the filtering rules are also met, the echo triggers the corresponding configuration.
help.about-can-be-emptied-detailed: Whether it is possible to clear the content in the field.
help.about-coding-format-detailed:
The print template does not support the following encodings:
EAN5,EAN2,UPCE,ITF14,MSI,MSI10,MSI11,MSI1010,MSI1110,PHARMACODE
help.about-combination-field-detailed: This attribute is used to combine fields. You can enter data from multiple fields to combine, or you can enter other character combinations.
help.about-company-detailed:
1) This attribute is used to specify the description of the field unit, such as currency: yuan, ten thousand yuan, percentage: %, etc.
2) When the unit has data, the location configuration item will be displayed.
3) There may be a display conflict between the current configuration item and the format setting after selecting the percentage. Please note that when the unit is percentage: %, it is best not to select the percentage in the format setting to avoid conflicts in the display effect.
help.about-component-name-detailed: The component name of the code that identifies the component application. Please follow the vue style. The letters are all lowercase and must contain a hyphen. This will help you avoid conflicts with current and future HTML elements.
help.about-component-path-detailed: The component path is the file under the views path. Invalid file in other path
help.about-configure-global-control-margins-d: 1) The following configuration adapts to all fields of the current form (except the grid layout).</br> 2) Configure the margins, the layout controls are the outer margins, and the rest of the controls are the inner margins, in pixels (px).</br> 3) Display the default margin when the bottom margin of the control is not set in the field. After setting the control margin, the bottom margin will prevail.</br> 4) Margin weight: Field Configuration (Control Margin)> Form Properties (Control Margin-Global)
help.about-control-hide-label-detailed: Whether the form field label is hidden.
help.about-control-label-width-detailed: The width of the form field label, for example: 50px. The form-item that is a direct child of Form will inherit this value.
help.about-control-margins-detailed: 1) After configuring the margins, add corresponding margins to the controls based on the original distances (the layout controls are the outer margins, and the rest of the controls are the inner margins), in pixels (px).</br> 2) Display the default margin when the bottom margin of the control is not set in the field. After setting the control margin, the bottom margin will prevail.</br> 3) Margin weight: Field Configuration (Control Margin)> Form Properties (Control Margin-Global)
help.about-control-width-detailed: The width of the control, for example: 200px.
help.about-covering-whole-line-detailed:
After checking this option, when there is no data or hidden data in one or more columns in the current grid layout, the width of the hidden column will be equally divided among the other displayed columns. If a column saves the original width, you can click [ 
Column configuration item] Check the [Unfilled] option in the configuration of the current column.
help.about-custom-class-detailed: You can define a custom style (class) for this field. The system form style cannot meet your requirements. You can dynamically insert the style through a custom form script.
help.about-custom-columns-detailed: You can define to show/hide the column data of the sub-table.
help.about-custom-dialog-detailed: This property configures a custom dialog box.</br> By selecting [Data Template] = "The type is the ‘Dialog’ type template</br>
help.about-custom-dialog-type-detailed: This attribute customizes the dialog box type.</br> [Custom Dialog]: Select [Data Template] = "Type as a ‘Dialog’ type template;</br>
help.about-custom-icons-detailed: The icon displayed by this attribute
help.about-data-dictionary-detailed: This attribute is used to bind the data dictionary.
help.about-data-filtering-detailed: By linking with the fields of the current form, the data of the associated data is filtered, and the data that meets the filter conditions are displayed in the associated field. If there are multiple data filter conditions, when querying, the conditions cannot be empty and only data that meets all the conditions at the same time are displayed.
help.about-data-format-detailed: The system will restrict the person who fills in the specified format of this field, and can also customize the regular expression.
help.about-data-template-detailed: When configuring the data template control, you must select the current option. When you select a data template with filter conditions, the following [Data Filtering] configuration item will be displayed, and the associated data can be configured to filter the filter conditions.
help.about-date-format-detailed:
This attribute is used to specify the date format</br>filled in this field
 There is a default format, and you can also customize the format.</br>The format reference is as follows:</br> format code | description | return value example</br> yyyy  four-digit year eg: 2014 or 2000</br>MM     Month, with leading zeros 01 to 12</br>M       Month, no leading zeros 1 to 12</br>dd     days, with leading zeros 01 to 31</br> d      days, without leading zeros 1 to 31</br>HH     Hour, 24-hour clock, with leading zeros 00 to 23</br>H       Hour, 24 hour clock, no leading zeros 0 to 23</br>mm     minutes, with leading zeros 00 to 59</br>m       minutes, no leading zeros 0 to 59</br>ss       seconds, with leading zeros 01 to 59</br>s        seconds, no leading zeros 1 to 59 [not supported]
help.about-default-display-detailed: When the sub-form has a grouping configuration, select this option to configure which grouping configuration the sub-form is displayed in by default.</br> If the [None] option is selected, or no selection is made, the sub-form is displayed as ungrouped when editing the page by default, and displayed as the first configuration in the group configuration when the detailed page is displayed.
help.about-default-value-detailed:
After setting, this value will be displayed as the default value in the initial value of the field.
If you do not need to set a default value, please leave this blank.
The default value type supports fixed value, dynamic script, data linkage, formula calculation, etc.
help.about-description-information-detailed: This attribute is used to specify some additional instructions for the field, and is generally used to guide the input of the fill-in.
help.about-display-fields-detailed: This attribute is used for sub-table display as display column display [valid in pop-up window mode].
help.about-display-information-detailed: When whether to display the auxiliary text and whether to display the current score is enabled at the same time, whether to display the auxiliary text will be invalid, and the score will be displayed first.
help.about-display-input-box: About whether to display the input box
help.about-display-input-box-detailed: The width of labels and controls must be greater than 200px after opening.
help.about-display-longitude-and-latitude-coo: About displaying latitude and longitude coordinates
After checking, you can get the latitude and longitude coordinates of the current location, and support 6 decimal places.
help.about-display-mode-detailed: This attribute is used to display the full path or only the selected node name when displaying the data.
help.about-dynamic-parameter-detailed: Need to configure to get data through the dynamic parameters of the form, you can do multi-level linkage.
help.about-edit-detailed: After checking, the control can be edited. If it is not checked, the control is read-only by default.
help.about-end-date-detailed: The system will limit the deadline (including this date) for the person who fills in this field.</br> This function does not do validity verification, please ensure by yourself: for a specific date, fill in the date consistent with the date format, and fill in numbers for other types.
help.about-feedback-icon-display-detailed: Whether to display the verification result feedback icon in the input box, only displayed in the input box.
help.about-field-identification-detailed: This attribute identifies the field attribute and is generally generated by the system without modification. By operating the identification attribute of the field through the form script, the field can be hidden/displayed.
help.about-file-upload-type-detailed: This attribute is used to limit the file upload type of the person who fills in.</br> Document types: txt, pdf, doc, docx, xls, xlsx, ppt, pptx, wps, htm, html, rtf, hlp.</br> Image category: jpg, jpeg, png, gif, bmp, psd, tif.</br> Video category: mkv, mp4, avi, swf, wmv, rmvb, mov, mpg.</br> Audio: mp3, flac, ape, wma, wav, aac, m4a, au, ram, mmf, aif.</br> Compressed package: rar, zip, 7z, gz, arj, z.</br> If the above format restrictions do not meet the requirements, it is recommended to select the [Custom] file upload type.</br> [Custom] file extension, please separate multiple files with commas, such as: txt, pdf, mp3, etc.</br>
help.about-fill-in-characters-at-most: Regarding the maximum number of characters
help.about-fill-in-characters-at-most-detaile: The system will limit the maximum number of characters that the person can fill in this field.
help.about-fine-tuning-detailed: The distance can be fine-tuned in the current positioning range.
help.about-fixed-column-detailed: The current configuration item is used to configure in the sub-table and the editing mode is in-table editing mode or pop-up mode, whether the current control column in the table is fixed on the left or right side of the table; the form editing mode is block mode, and the form In the case of grouping or the form is one-to-one, the current configuration items are invalid.
help.about-form-background-color-detailed: You can specify a specific color as the background color inside the form, and you can control the transparency.
help.about-form-options-detailed: You can specify styles for the options of single-select controls or multiple-select controls.
help.about-form-rules-detailed: Form rules Set rules for fields (text box, single item selection, drop-down box, etc.):</br> 1. When the form field data meets the form rules, the specified field will be displayed (hide) according to the rules, or the color and background color of the field will be changed.</br> 2. The form will only execute one form rule. When multiple form rules are met, they are executed according to the ordering priority of the form rules. The smaller the sequence number of the form rule, the higher the priority.</br> 3. When changing the configured control fields, you need to reconfigure the form rules.</br> 4. When business rules are mutually exclusive, data cannot be known in advance, and verification can only be triggered in actual operations.</br> 5. When the rule is set to display only, the set form field must have display permission. Hidden fields cannot be displayed.
help.about-form-script-detailed: The form script can be extended with custom scripts. Satisfy the functions that the form cannot achieve.
help.about-form-shadow-detailed: After opening, the form will have a shadow.
help.about-form-submission-verification-detai: A series of conditions are checked for validity when the form is submitted.
help.about-format-of-Statistics-detailed: Format the number statistics of the current subform control list, the [total statistics] in the text on the right represents the total number of data in the list.
help.about-format-of-generated-code: About the format of the generated code
help.about-format-of-generated-code-detailed: After selecting this item, click the [Generate Code] button to display the generated code as a pop-up window.
help.about-frame-detailed: You can set the border thickness and border color for the form.
help.about-global-field-detailed: The user's setting field option and the configuration of the field option are based on the field setting or the global one.
help.about-global-label-detailed: The configuration of user and setting field labels and field selection is based on the field setting or the global one.
help.about-group-additional-information-displ: After setting the list grouping, you can configure custom group display information (additional information).
help.about-group-additional-information-forma: After setting the list grouping, you can configure custom group display information (additional information).</br> When configuring custom group display information, the format can be the result of one field or several fields, or a script written by yourself.</br> Formula: Use formulas to calculate and splice the fields of the current grouped data, and display the results.</br> Script: Improve the default function and use the returned result as additional information.
help.about-group-header-information-display-d: After setting the list grouping, you can configure custom group display information (main information of the header).</br> The header information only selects the first data field in the same group. Therefore, please configure the same fields that are shared by the current group.</br> Warm reminder: You can choose the field as the grouping condition as the header information.
help.about-grouping-conditions-detailed: After setting the list grouping, you need to select the condition basis for the field to be used for grouping. At least one field must be selected, otherwise all data will be grouped into one group by default when querying the group, and the header information will display ‘unknown group data’.
help.about-header-image-detailed:
You can upload a picture as the header picture of the form.
The recommended image width is 1600px, and the height is unlimited
help.about-header-style-detailed: You can use text or pictures as the header of the form, which is more conducive to brand promotion.
help.about-height-detailed: The system will set according to the set height, the default height is 150px.
help.about-hide-detailed: After checking, the field will be hidden, but if it is dynamically assigned, you can assign a value to the field.
help.about-hide-dividing-line-detailed: The dividing line between the name and the online form, detail form or data template in the control. If the name is hidden, the dividing line will also be hidden.
help.about-hide-required-asterisks-detailed: This attribute is used to set whether the form label displays a red asterisk next to required fields
help.about-horizontal-alignment-detailed: Support left, center, right, equal spacing on both sides, and justified at both ends.
help.about-image-upload-format-detailed: This attribute is used for the image upload format.</br> [Note] When customizing the format, the format is'.' + custom file suffix</br> [Type]: .jpg, .jpeg, .png, .bmp, etc.</br>
help.about-index-detailed: You can define the sequence number of the display list.
help.about-initialization-validation-detailed: This option is used to configure whether to perform initial verification of the form after entering the form.
help.about-initialize-build-number-detailed: This attribute is used for automatic numbering whether to enter the interface to initialize the number, or to generate the number after submitting to the background.
help.about-label-description-location-detaile: This attribute is used to set the description of the form tag.</br> Label icon: There is a prompt icon behind the label;</br> Bottom row: In the bottom row of the form field.
help.about-label-location-detailed: After setting the customization, configure the current option to determine whether the formatted data is placed in front of [label text], if not selected, it will be placed at the back by default.
help.about-label-text-detailed: This attribute is used to tell the person who fills in what kind of content should be entered in the field.</br> is usually one or two short words, but it can also be a question.
help.about-layout-patterns-detailed:
Support Flex layout and default (div) layout,
Flex layout: Allows the horizontal alignment of child elements within the parent node-left, center, right, equal spacing on both sides, and justified at both ends. Between sub-elements and sub-elements, top alignment, vertical center alignment, and bottom alignment are supported. Flex layout is based on 24 grids to define the width of each "box", but it is not limited to the grid.
help.about-left-and-right-spacing: About the left and right intervals
help.about-left-and-right-spacing-detailed: Set the left and right spacing between fields in the grid.
help.about-linkage-data-detailed: The configuration linkage data control refers to a field of other forms, and the value changes and will follow the corresponding field value of the associated form. The changed field will store the current value and will not change in real time. Note that the returned field types must match.
help.about-linked-data-detailed: The associated data source is the information in "Data Template Management" and the template type is "Value Source".
help.about-linkquery-column-detailed: Select which fields in the associated data need to be displayed.
help.about-list-grouping-detailed: When the sub-form is in table edit mode or pop-up window mode, set whether the list is grouped.
help.about-manage-column-names-detailed: You can define the name of the management column and the width of the management column
help.about-manage-style-display-detailed: This property controls the layout style of the subform row data manipulation buttons
help.about-maximum-area-detailed: This attribute is used to set the maximum area for address selection.
help.about-maximum-area-value-detailed: This attribute is used to set the value of a range on the largest area of address selection.
help.about-maximum-detailed: The system will limit the maximum number of people who fill in this field.
help.about-maximum-number-of-uploaded-files: Regarding the maximum number of uploaded files
help.about-maximum-number-of-uploaded-files-d: This attribute is used to limit the maximum number of files uploaded by the person who fills in. If the number is not filled, the default is no limit.
help.about-minimum-area-detailed: This attribute is used to set the minimum area for address selection.
help.about-minimum-characters-detailed: The system will limit the minimum number of characters to fill in this field.
help.about-minimum-term-detailed: The system will restrict the person who fills in to check the least allowed options in this field.
help.about-minimum-value-detailed: The system will restrict those who fill in the minimum value of this field.
help.about-mobile-display-detailed: The mobile terminal will display according to the attribute.
help.about-multi-level-header-detailed: After setting the multi-level header, custom columns, sorting, and grouping do not take effect.
help.about-multiple-choice-detailed: This attribute is used to restrict whether multiple values can be selected for filling, or only one value can be selected.
help.about-number-of-data-detailed: The number of data items is divided into one and multiple items. There may be multiple pieces of data filtered through data filtering conditions. If multiple pieces of data need to be displayed, select "Multiple items".
help.about-number-of-rows-detailed: The number of rows displayed in the multi-line text box.
help.about-object-properties-detailed: This property is used to bind business object properties and is used to submit the data binding object name.
help.about-on-decimal-places-detailed: Enter the decimal place, the system will limit the last few decimal places, will check the validity of the value, and will prompt if the number of digits is exceeded.
help.about-option-data-value-source: About the option data value source
help.about-option-data-value-source-detailed: This attribute is used to set whether the option data value source is a custom fixed option value/label [static data], or through the [value source] type of the [data template].
help.about-options-styles-detailed: You can set the option style of the field, the default method is still the button method.
help.about-other-option-fields-detailed: The input box behind the other options is related to the field selected by the current configuration item. The displayed value in the input box is consistent with the value of the field. It is recommended to select a field that is not displayed in the current designer
help.about-paging-detailed: When the sub-form list is grouped, this option is invalid; this option is to set whether the list is displayed in pages.
help.about-picture-prompt-information-detaile: This attribute is used to set the information displayed in the selected picture.
help.about-picture-quantity-limit: About the limit of the number of pictures
help.about-picture-quantity-limit-detailed: This attribute is used to limit the maximum number of images uploaded.
help.about-picture-size-detailed: This attribute is used to limit the image size.</br> [Unit]: M </br>
help.about-placeholder-detailed: This attribute is used to specify text prompt for this field, and prompt inside the text.</br> Generally, it is "please enter", "please select", etc. It is recommended not to exceed 200 characters.
help.about-position-detailed:
1) This attribute is used to specify the display position configuration of the field unit. For example, the label is displayed in the label, the data before the data is displayed in front of the field data, the data after the data is displayed after the field data, and the control is displayed in the Behind the data entry box.
2) If no location is selected, it will be displayed in the label by default.
help.about-presentation-form-detailed: This attribute is used in the display form of the data dictionary, which can be displayed as labels, icons, buttons, etc.
help.about-primary-key-detailed: This attribute is used to identify the primary key field as a unique identifier.
help.about-priority-detailed: The smaller the priority number, the earlier the form rule will be validated. When multiple rules are met at the same time, the lower priority will be selected according to the highest priority. If the priority is the same, the rule with the highest position will be selected.
help.about-proportion-of-width-detailed: You can define how much the page width the field occupies in the fill-in page. The system uses a grid layout of 24 columns.
help.about-reactive-layouts-detailed: Refer to Bootstrap's responsive design, and preset five response sizes: xs sm md lg xl.
help.about-read-only-detailed: When checked, the field will be read-only, if not checked, the field is writable by default.
help.about-read-only-show-style-detailed:
This attribute is used to set the read-only display style of the form field. 
</br>
      
Text display: The display form is in text form;</br>
      
Display as it is: The display format is the same as the editing method, but it is forbidden.
help.about-required-verification-detailed:
After checking, the field will not be allowed to be empty, and a red asterisk (*) will be marked in front of the field name.
If the person who fills in the required field does not enter the required field when submitting the form, the system will give a relevant error prompt and the form will not be submitted.
This attribute is often used in a field that must be entered by the person who needs to be forced to fill in.
help.about-script-type-detailed: The script type of the click event, and the action to be triggered afterwards.
help.about-select-form-detailed: When configuring the online form/detail form control, the current option must be selected.
help.about-selection-mode-detailed: This attribute is used to restrict the person who fills in can only choose leaf nodes or arbitrary nodes.
help.about-selector-type-detailed: This attribute is used for the selector type.</br>Currently supports user, organization, position, and role selectors.
help.about-separator-detailed: This attribute is used to display the separator of the complete path of the data display, the default is'/'.
help.about-serial-number-detailed: This attribute is used to bind the serial number, and the automatic generation of codes can be easily realized through the serial number field.
help.about-set-association-configuration-deta: A unique identifier and display value need to be configured. The unique identifier is the unique identifier of the field storage database (not necessarily the id or the primary key, it can be a unique identifier such as a number), and the display value is used as a displayed field.
help.about-set-positioning-range-detailed: You can add multiple positioning keywords, and pass the verification when the positioning position meets one of the keywords.
help.about-set-style-detailed: This property is used to set the dividing line style of the field.
help.about-show-word-limit-detailed: This property is used to set whether the field displays the input word count. Note: To take effect, you need to set [Verification Rules] to fill in the maximum length to set the length, otherwise it will be invalid
help.about-simple-style-detailed: Set a simple style, under this condition, the center alignment/description/spacing/display direction will be invalid.
help.about-single-file-sizes: About the size of a single file
help.about-single-file-sizes-detailed: This attribute is used to limit the size of a single file of the person who fills in, the unit is M.</br> You can choose according to the type of files you need to collect, for example, a photo is about 3MB, and a 3-minute mp3 audio is about 5MB.
help.about-slider-detailed: The minimum and maximum values set must be integer multiples of the step size
help.about-spacing-detailed: The spacing of each step bar (step) supports a percentage. If it is not filled in, the spacing will be adaptive.
help.about-start-date-detailed: The system will limit the starting date range (including this date) for filling in this field.</br> This function does not do validity verification, please ensure by yourself: for a specific date, fill in a date consistent with the date format; fill in numbers for other types.
